South Africa Asks Brazil to Back Manuel for IMF Job, People’s Daily Says

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-06-03T13:09:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-03/south-africa-asks-brazil-to-back-manuel-for-imf-job-people-s-daily-says.html
South African President  Jacob Zuma 
called his Brazilian counterpart,  Dilma Rousseff , yesterday to
support former Finance Minister  Trevor Manuel  to head the
International Monetary Fund, the People’s Daily reported, citing
Rousseff’s spokesman, Rodrigo Baena.  Rousseff said  Brazil  wouldn’t make a decision until all
candidates for the position had applied, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nasreen Seria at 
 nseria@bloomberg.net  